      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Former Victorian LOUIE LOU I NZ (8) made a strong start for the new yard when he raced parked from this barrier and stuck on for a 3.4m second at this circuit and distance. That was his first outing for eight weeks so it should have improved him. Can go one better. GOLDEN TRIBE (6) continues to perform well and looks close to a win after coming from a wider barrier for a 1.5m second here last week. Draws lower and is suited dropping to a distance where he is a three-time winner. MAJOR ART NZ (4) draws much better than he did last start and had been racing well prior so is worth another chance. SUGAR PIE HONEY (9) has been struggling for form so far this campaign but is a Group 1 winner at this circuit and distance so would win this if anywhere near her best.",
